pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates

Class DomainConsistencyPredicate

  • java.lang.Object
    • pt.ist.fenixframework.core.AbstractDomainObject
      • pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates.DomainConsistencyPredicate_Base
        • pt.ist.fenixframework.consistencyPredicates.DomainConsistencyPredicate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, DomainObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrivateConsistencyPredicate_Base, PublicConsistencyPredicate_Base

    public abstract class DomainConsistencyPredicate
extends DomainConsistencyPredicate_Base
    A DomainConsistencyPredicate is the persistent domain entity that represents a consistency predicate method inside a domain class. The DomainFenixFrameworkRoot uses this entity after each initialization, to determine which predicates were already known, and which are new.

      • executeConsistencyPredicateForMetaClassAndSubclasses

        public abstract void executeConsistencyPredicateForMetaClassAndSubclasses(DomainMetaClass metaClass)
        Executes this consistency predicate for all objects of the given DomainMetaClass, and objects of subclasses. The predicate will NOT be executed for objects of any subclass that overrides this consistency predicate.
        Parameters:
        metaClass - the DomainMetaClass for which to execute this predicate.

      • checkOverridingMethods

        public abstract void checkOverridingMethods(DomainMetaClass metaClass)
        Checks all the subclasses of this consistency predicate for any methods that override it. For each method found, checks that it has the ConsistencyPredicate annotation.
        Throws:
        Error - if this predicate is being overridden by a non-predicate method

      • executeConsistencyPredicateForExistingDomainObjects

        protected void executeConsistencyPredicateForExistingDomainObjects(DomainMetaClass metaClass)
        Executes this consistency predicate for all objects in the given List. For each object, after the execution, this method creates a DomainDependenceRecord based on the dependencies of that object.
        Parameters:
        metaClass - the DomainMetaClass of DomainObject for which to execute this predicate.

      • delete

        public void delete()
        Deletes this DomainConsistencyPredicate.
        A DomainConsistencyPredicate should be deleted when the consistency predicate method is removed from the code, or the containing class is removed. In either case, the framework can delete all the associated DomainDependenceRecords.
        This method is called when the predicate is being removed, and not the class.
        See Also:
        classDelete()

      • classDelete

        public void classDelete()
        Deletes this DomainConsistencyPredicate.
        A DomainConsistencyPredicate should be deleted when the consistency predicate method is removed from the code, or the containing class is removed. In either case, the framework can delete all the associated DomainDependenceRecords.
        This method is called when the predicate's class is being removed.
        See Also:
        delete()
